---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { config } from '../config';
---

<Layout
  title="Delete Your Account - BuildWorkPro"
  description="How to permanently delete your BuildWorkPro account and the personal data associated with it."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Delete Your Account</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Last Updated: June 20, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-headings:font-semibold prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-brand-600"
      >
        <p>
          You can permanently delete your BuildWorkPro account and the personal data associated with
          it at any time. This page explains who can delete an account, how to do it from inside the
          mobile app, and what happens to your data afterward.
        </p>

        <h2>Who can delete an account</h2>
        <p>
          Any signed-in BuildWorkPro user can request deletion of their own account. If you are the
          <strong>only administrator</strong> of an organization, you must first promote another member
          to administrator (or close the organization) so it is never left without an administrator. The
          app will tell you if this applies to you and will not delete your account until ownership has
          been transferred.
        </p>

        <h2>How to delete your account from the app</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Open the BuildWorkPro mobile app and sign in.</li>
          <li>Go to the <strong>More</strong> tab.</li>
          <li>Under <strong>Account</strong>, tap <strong>Delete Account</strong>.</li>
          <li>Confirm when prompted.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>What happens when you delete</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Immediately:</strong> your account is disabled — you are signed out on every device
            and can no longer sign in.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>30-day grace period:</strong> your data is scheduled for permanent deletion 30 days
            later. During this window you may contact us to cancel the deletion and restore access.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>After 30 days:</strong> your personal account data is permanently deleted. Business
            records that belong to your organization (for example projects, invoices, and records other
            members rely on) are retained by the organization as required for its operation and for legal
            and accounting obligations, as described in our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>A confirmation email is sent when deletion is scheduled.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>If you can&rsquo;t access the app</h2>
        <p>
          If you are unable to sign in to complete the steps above, email
          <a href={`mailto:${config.email.support}`}>{config.email.support}</a> from the address on your
          account and we will process the deletion request for you.
        </p>

        <h2>Questions</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, contact <a href={`mailto:${config.email.privacy}`}
            >{config.email.privacy}</a
          >. See our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for full details on what data we collect,
          how long we keep it, and your rights.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
